    0, "Emergency Support Function 8 (ESF-8) is one of 15 ESFs in the National Response Framework (NRF). ESF-8 - Public Health and Medical Services: (1) Lead agency: Department of Health and Human Services (HHS), specifically the Administration for Strategic Preparedness and Response (ASPR); (2) Scope: coordinating federal public health and medical support for state, tribal, and local jurisdictions during disasters; (3) Capabilities include: assessment of public health and medical needs; health surveillance; medical care personnel deployment (DMAT, DMORT, VPDS); health and medical equipment and supplies; patient evacuation and definitive care; safety and security of human drugs, biologics, and medical devices; blood and blood products; food safety; agriculture safety; mental/behavioral health; mass fatality management; veterinary medical support; (4) Key resources: National Disaster Medical System (NDMS); Strategic National Stockpile (SNS); DMATs; DMORTs; Federal Medical Stations (FMS). ESF-8 integrates with state ESF-8 and healthcare coalitions during response.", "Identify ESF-8 as the federal Public Health and Medical Services function led by HHS/ASPR that coordinates medical response resources during disasters", "Incident Command System (ICS)", 2, "recall",
